<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - FRONT DRIVE AXLE: SPICER S-9000 - PINION DISASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="10">
        <title>PINION DISASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Use
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0200913">Figure 13</hotlnk>
            as a reference to disassemble the pinion.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0200913" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0200913" filename="../figg02/G0200913.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 13. Pinion Disassembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. PINION NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. FLAT WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. OIL SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEX BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>5. BEARING CUP (PINION INNER AND OUTER)</callout1>
                <callout1>6. BEARING RETAINER CAP</callout1>
                <callout1>7. PINION BEARING SPACER</callout1>
                <callout1>8. BEARING CONE (INNER AND OUTER)</callout1>
                <callout1>9. PINION</callout1>
                <callout1>10. BEARING ASSEMBLY (STRAIGHT ROLLER)</callout1>
                <callout1>11. HEX BOLT, CARRIER MOUNTING</callout1>
                <callout1>12. FLAT WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>13. SHIM (PINION POSITION)</callout1>
                <callout1>14. CARRIER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove pinion cage capscrews which hold pinion assembly to the carrier housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200914">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200914" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200914" filename="../figg02/G0200914.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Remove Capscrews</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove pinion and cage assembly from carrier housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200915">Figure 15</hotlnk>). If difficulty is encountered in removing pinion assembly
                from carrier housing, place brass drift on inner end of pinion gear and tap lightly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200916">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200915" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200915" filename="../figg02/G0200915.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Remove Pinion and Cage Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0200916" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200916" filename="../figg02/G0200916.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Tap Lightly on End of Gear</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Retain shims for possible use during reassembly.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount pinion assembly in a soft jawed vise, holding yoke stationary, and remove nut and
                washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200917">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200917" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200917" filename="../figg02/G0200917.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Remove Nut and Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the end yoke using a suitable puller.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove pinion gear from cage assembly.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It may be necessary to tap outer end pinion gear with a soft hammer. Replace pinion nut, flush
                        with end of pinion, so damage to threads does not occur.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Located between pinion bearings is a selective spacer, used for pinion bearing preload.
                Retain this spacer for possible use in reassembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200918">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200918" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200918" filename="../figg02/G0200918.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Retain Selective Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove old pinion oil seal and discard. Always replace it with a new seal at time of
                reassembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift out outer pinion bearing cone.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove inner pinion bearing cup; use a suitable adapter and press or puller (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200919">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200919" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200919" filename="../figg02/G0200919.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Use Press or Puller</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not nick bearing bore.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove outer pinion bearing cup (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200920">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200920" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200920" filename="../figg02/G0200920.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Remove Outer Pinion Bearing Cup</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not nick bearing bore.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove pinion roller bearing from end of pinion (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200921">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200921" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200921" filename="../figg02/G0200921.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Remove Pinion Roller Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove inner bearing cone from pinion gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200922">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200922" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200922" filename="../figg02/G0200922.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Remove Inner Bearing Cone</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
